My bash configuration.

To get started:
1. Apply settings/simple.theme
2. ln -s /full/path/to/bashrc ~/.bashrc
3. ln -s /full/path/to/bash_profile ~/.bash_profile
4. ln -s /full/path/to/bash ~/.bash
5. ln -s /full/path/to/inputrc ~/.inputrc
5. chmod 755 ~/.bash/bin/*
6. Install Brew
7. brew install bash
8. brew install fasd
9. brew install vcprompt
10. Install RVM

After running brew install bash, you can change the default shell safely by:
1. Add /usr/local/bin/bash to /etc/shells
2. Running chsh -s /usr/local/bin/bash.
